A 12-year-old boy was electrocuted and passed away at Illovo Beach on Saturday evening, 22 February. KwaZulu-Natal provincial police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala said: “It is alleged that on 22 February at 22.50, a 12-year-old boy was electrocuted while at Illovo.” Captain Charlene Van Der Spuy of Amanzimtoti SAPS confirmed that the police attended to a complaint at Illovo Beach that night. ” On their arrival, they met with the paramedics of Netcare who confirmed that a 12-year-old boy was declared deceased after being electrocuted by the electrical fencing on the property, ” said Van Der Spuy. A case of Inquest was opened for investigation by Amanzimtoti SAPS,